The paper deals with the calibration-free compensation of field inhomogeneity artifacts in Echo Planar Imaging (EPI) MRI data. This involves the recovery of an image time series from highly undersampled Fourier measurements, which is a problem commonly addressed in the computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. The proposed approach also involves exploiting the low rank property of a structured multi-fold Toeplitz matrix, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper introduces a fast two-step algorithm for matrix completion, which is a problem commonly studied in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
